How many smooth solutions does the following initial-boundary-value problem have?
\begin{equation*}
\begin{cases}
u_{tt}+2023u_t-u_{xx}=0~~~&t\in(0,T), x\in(0,\pi)\\
u(0,x)=\varphi(x),~u_t(0,x)=\psi(x)~~~&x\in [0,\pi]\\
u(t,0)=u(t,\pi)=0~~~&t\in[0,T].
\end{cases}
\end{equation*}
Here $ \varphi(x) $ and $\psi(x)$ are smooth functions satisfying $ \varphi(0) = \varphi(\pi) = 0 $ and $ \psi(0) = \psi(\pi) = 0 $.
